18/04/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic said Sunday (17 April) that he believes in Serbia's commitment to enhanced co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. 
He also predicted that the EU ministerial council would acknowledge progress achieved recently and support the start of Stabilisation and Association Agreement talks with Serbia-Montenegro when a vote is taken on 25 April. 
Djukanovic's statement came a day before EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn visits the federal union.
In other news, Montenegrin police chief Dragan Djurovic said Friday that Podgorica is committed to fighting terrorism and trafficking. 
He met to discuss bilateral co-operation issues with Iran's Ambassador to Serbia-Montenegro, Mortez Mir Heydari. 
(Tanjug - 17/04/05; Mina, Montenegrin Government Web site - 15/04/05)
